{"name":"Spell Finesse","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>The hero is particularly adept with one power.</p>\n<p>This Edge may be chosen once per rank. Each time he picks this Edge he may pick one of the options below and apply it to one power he knows. Each option may only be picked once per individual power, but the same option can be applied to different spells and different options can be given to the same spell. For instance, a mage can take an increased Wild Die and AP 2 for his <em>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.TbcqRtdavoGl7niL]{Bolt}&nbsp;</em>spell, but he cannot take AP 2 twice.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Arcane:</strong> The hero increases his arcane skill Wild Die by one die type when casting the spell.</li>\n<li><strong>Armor Penetration: </strong>A damaging spell has AP 2. This counts against Armor provided by Arcane Resistance and stacks with any other similar bonus, such as an acid trapping.</li>\n<li><strong>Heavy Weapon: </strong>A damaging spell counts as a Heavy Weapon. It does not gain any AP value.</li>\n<li><strong>Range: </strong>The hero treats his relevant attribute as one step higher for the purpose of determining the spell&rsquo;s Range. Fixed range spells (such as bolt) have their range increased by 2/4/8. Touch and Self spells are unaffected by this ability.</li>\n<li><strong>Selective: </strong>When casting a spell with a template effect, the caster decides who is and isn&rsquo;t affected, to a maximum of half his arcane skill die. For instance, a mage with an arcane skill of d8 can drop a <em>blast </em>over a group of allies and foes and cause no damage to four of his comrades.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Arcane Background, arcane skill d8+, Arcana d8+"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_pi4ivmcmcvb","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"0SGFP8nhMBqqr2sK"}
{"name":"#[CF_tempEntity]","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"","range":"","rof":1,"ap":0,"minStr":"","shots":0,"currentShots":0},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nth9juzzfye","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000","name":"Background Edges","children":["TZLi9seMbm1aMBJx","ZOoUAEvz3bGkeW6k","bBwDM4fIwya3waIl","XNLnKWtd80HhmNxO","wLgGbaLP541KdtqR","YTHy8F3gmnmr1Uei","gn4HeWXp8YNwP65B","1Fpvm2JI7tmMU65u","jrjtQewN5V05tHCV","6KX3BMOvFpOGOTSH","NY0rWJ5djDyEyRkc"],"folderPath":["temp_oereppnkt5p"]}},"effects":[],"_id":"11tvYbY2Z9IOEjbI"}
{"name":"Aristocrat","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>This individual was born into privilege or came into it later in life. She may or may not have money (the Rich or Filthy Rich Edge), but she still walks in the elite social circles of the setting.</p>\n<p>This character will likely be able to place ir' before their last name to denote being a member of the nobility.</p>\n<p>Aristocrats add +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.VrOjvkSpawKmH4go]{Persuasion} when @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Networking]{Networking} with the local elite, captains of industry, nobles, or other aristocrats. They also add +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.fqYNzAjIQz8lKOBj]{Common Knowledge} rolls made to know the etiquette of the upper class, recognize family trees or heraldry, or recall gossip concerning others of their station.</p>\n<p>Typically, a character with this edge has the lowest noble title (his father being one or two steps higher up the social ladder). The character also rules a small manor, small village, or hamlet. Only with the GM's permission may the character begin at a higher social status.</p>\n<p>Further social promotions require family members to move aside (or die) to allow the character to assume a new title, and this should be worked into the campaign.</p>\n<h2>Other Form of \"Nobility\"</h2>\n<p>While the Noble Edge typically covers those born to high station, this is not a firm dictate. The Edge can also be used to represent other character types. A player who wants to use the Noble Edge in an atypical way should always consult with his GM first.</p>\n<p>For instance, a cleric with the Edge may be the head of a small temple. A hero may also be a guildmaster. Normally this should be a legitimate guild, but with the GM's permission, the hero may run a small thieves' guild. A hero may be a guildmaster for a craft guild or perhaps run a way station for one of the dragonmarked houses. The hero must handle labor disputes, raids by the thieves' guild, and so on.</p>\n<p>Although a merchant can be represented by the Rich Edge, one taking the Aristocract Edge might be a well-known merchant or have a sizable business. In return for the +2 Networking bonus, he also has the hassle of balancing the books, negotiating contracts, fighting off competitors, and such like.</p>\n<p>Characters using Artistocract in an alternate way do not gain the titles listed elsewhere. GMs and players should work together to create suitable honorifics.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Modified from Savage Worlds Adventure Edition</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nth9juzzfye","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"1Fpvm2JI7tmMU65u"}
{"name":"Master Necromancer","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Zombies raised by the Necromancer now have an extra die in @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.9IwLt34etK096UAK]{Strength} and one skill of his choice (usually @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.xCkOFlFmE1WwGXq6]{Fighting}).</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Horror Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Necromancer"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_04a7imn3lagw","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"1LEO5mLFXoNKFoZf"}
{"name":"Familiar","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>The mage has acquired an animal familiar. The creature gained varies with the mage's Rank when he first takes this Edge. Use the Available Familiars table to determine the type of animal a mage can choose.</p>\n<p>The mage and the familiar acquire the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.9NdXyRvT8uGXmi33]{Loyal} Hindrance with regard to each other. The familiar is not a slave, however, and can refuse to follow orders, especially ones which will cause it harm. Unless ordered otherwise, the familiar follows its natural instincts. For example, a cat familiar may stop to chase a mouse, take a quick nap, or sate its curiosity about a small hole, and it's likely to hide during combat.</p>\n<p>The strong bond allows the familiar to resist the effects of beast friend. Each Rank of the mage adds +1 to the creature's Size for the purpose of how many Power Points are needed to control it.</p>\n<p>Both can understand each other's speech. To others, the familiar is simply making animal noises - the mage speaks his normal language.</p>\n<p>The familiar is a Wild Card with respect to wounds and the Wild Die, but has no bennies. The mage may spend his for the familiar, however.</p>\n<p>A mage can dismiss a familiar to gain another if he chooses.</p>\n<p>Each additional time this Edge is taken, the mage can pick one of the powers below. Each power may only be taken once. The mage may take this Edge only once each Rank. Taking it during character creation allows the character to take it again while he's a Novice.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The mage can transfer wounds and Fatigue levels to or from his familiar as a free action.</li>\n<li>The mage may increase one attribute of his choice which is lower than that of the familiar by one die, to a maximum of d12.</li>\n<li>The mage can use the familiar's senses as if they were his own. This requires concentration. The maximum range for this ability is the mage's Smarts x 100 yards.</li>\n<li>The familiar can use the mage's Combat Edges as its own.</li>\n<li>Any spells the mage casts on himself also affect the familiar. If he casts armor with a raise, both he and his familiar gain +4 Armor for the duration, for example.</li>\n<li>The familiar has 5 Power Points, which the mage may use as if they were his own. They recharge at the same rate as the mage's (usually 1 per hour).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Arcane Background (Magic), Arcana d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_04a7imn3lagw","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"2ywaMUeZjvavgMvQ"}
{"name":"Charge","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>The character knows how to deliver a well-aimed blow at the end of a charge.</p>\n<p>If the hero performs a run action and ends his movement for the round adjacent to an opponent, he may make a single @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.xCkOFlFmE1WwGXq6]{Fighting} roll as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.E5UTH6Wqsi9DYlEN]{free action} (no @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.On57BX9RxFSOBjzj]{multi-action} penalty). This cannot be combined with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.XcO1OKzJmCozkpTJ]{Frenzy} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.5TWI3a1ZN23CpcVL]{Sweep}.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Rassilon Expansion II</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Vigor d8+, Fighting d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nslc8pagbdr","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"3sdEj0DW8JCA1QxO"}
{"name":"#[CF_tempEntity]","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"","range":"","rof":1,"ap":0,"minStr":"","shots":0,"currentShots":0},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_yuhzeq47stf","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Weird Edges","color":"#000000","name":"Weird Edges","children":["XFrEiuzllUrAkVJu","mRlUe9x35X34BB5b","phOgZZTXELUps6zh"],"folderPath":["temp_oereppnkt5p"]}},"effects":[],"_id":"4FkmGrQTlkEHYZjy"}
{"name":"Enchant","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Enchant allows a character to craft \"enchanted items.\" These are devices which essentially allow the user&mdash;whether he's a spellcaster or not&mdash;to cast whatever power the item is imbued with.</p>\n<p>They require an item that was crafted with a raise. Each @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.ZUQ9fsJ5ybqBIByu]{Power Point} stored into the item requires are least 25 galifars of Eberron Dragonshards. Each die type for the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.ZUQ9fsJ5ybqBIByu]{Arcane Skill}&nbsp;roll requires and additional 50 galifars of Eberron Dragonshards up to the a maximum die type of what the caster has at the time of its creation. The crafter has to have the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.k4FQeOuzmYAhVaLF]{Power} available to be able to enchant an item.</p>\n<p class=\"embedded-example\"><strong>Example: </strong>An artificer with a d10 in Magecraft can enchant a permanent bolt wand with a d8 Arcane skill for 200 galfiars and 10 power points an additional 250 galifars.</p>\n<p>Items created through this Edge are referred to as minor artifacts. Items recharge at the standard rate of one power Point per hour. The wielder cannot use his own @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.ZUQ9fsJ5ybqBIByu]{Power Points}&nbsp;with enchanted items&mdash;they are effectively \"locked.\"</p>\n<p>While a character can add further powers to his own devices, he cannot alter those of others.</p>\n<p><strong>Malfunction:</strong> Items created in this way fail to activate if the arcane skill die roll is a 1, regardless of the Wild Die, but have no further ill effects.</p>\n<p>The user can decide which powers he's activating when he makes his arcane skill roll, however. He may also make a single roll for all the powers the device has. If a hero carries a ring enchanted with invisibility and armor, for example, both powers must share its pool of Power Points, but the wearer can decide whether to activate only one of its powers or both with a single roll.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Gear Toolkit</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Dragonmakr of Making, Magic, Magecraft, or Miracles), Arcana d6+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_pi4ivmcmcvb","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"4GGbQg3WXbEZwW3D"}
{"name":"Skald","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Skalds are storytellers and poets and artists, able to recounter epic poems, plays, stories, legends, and other information from memory. Skalds learn special techniques for memorizing things he has heard or read, and is well versed in many topics.</p>\n<p>Pick any one of the following skills: @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.fqYNzAjIQz8lKOBj]{Common Knowledge}, Lore, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.LAPnQmjS9mpK7tzl]{Performance}, or Traditions and add +2 to the total whenever they're used.</p>\n<p>Additionally they may split their skill into two @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.qfnDbhOjzlgycFPJ]{Skill Specializations} as appropiate.</p>\n<p>This Edge may be taken more than once if applied to different skills.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Performance d6+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_04a7imn3lagw","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"4R3dFCrIbQMim4gk"}
{"name":"Sucker Punch","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>The character doesn't know the meaning of the words \"fair fight.\" If he succeeds in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.XbY9qh8iHoDcbM5c]{Test} against an adjacent opponent, the character receives a free @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.xCkOFlFmE1WwGXq6]{Fighting} attack. This attack does not incur a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.On57BX9RxFSOBjzj]{multi-action penalty}.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Slipstream Player's Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, First Strike, Agility d6+, Fighting d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nslc8pagbdr","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"53lHBWQGKvV56UTA"}
{"name":"Rope Monkey","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Rope Monkeys are those sailors who may as well have been born in the rigging. They always seem to know just the right rope to cut and pull to swing to some other part of the ship and can ride the lines down to avoid an otherwise nasty fall.</p>\n<p>Rope Monkey has two functions. The first is to allow a character on the exterior of the ship to move to any other exposed part of the ship by swinging from the rigging. This counts as the character&rsquo;s movement and requires a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.npGSR7Ru0Jl4LUXq]{Athletics} roll. If successful, he moves to any other external area of the ship. He may not move further this action even by \"running.\" With a raise, he can move and gains momentary surprise on any foes, adding +2 to any @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.xCkOFlFmE1WwGXq6]{Fighting} attacks and damage rolls for the round. This can also be combined with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.XbY9qh8iHoDcbM5c]{Test} maneuver.</p>\n<p>Rope Monkeys may also use this ability in forests with tall trees. In that case, the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.npGSR7Ru0Jl4LUXq]{Athletics} roll is made at &ndash;2 and the character may reposition himself within d10\".</p>\n<p>A foe who wants to take his free attack at a Rope Monkey swinging out of melee must subtract 2 from his roll. The same applies to characters with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.R0tfd1gh2HarRjsa]{First Strike}&mdash;they suffer a &ndash;2 penalty to their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.xCkOFlFmE1WwGXq6]{Fighting} roll.</p>\n<p>Rope Monkeys may also make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.npGSR7Ru0Jl4LUXq]{Athletics} roll any time they fall from a ship&rsquo;s rigging (and are conscious). Success means they take half the usual @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.aaw7J8vVCbE0mqsY]{falling} damage by grabbing onto ropes as they tumble. With a raise, the sailor manages to slide down a rope and suffers no damage.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: 50 Fathoms</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Agility d8+, Athletics d10+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_04a7imn3lagw","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"5t6YN7l206IlOWXx"}
{"name":"Mighty Shot","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>The hero has learned how to use his full strength with a bow. The character calculates damage with his bow as Str+d6, instead of a flat 2d6.</p>\n<p>Mighty shot does not work with crossbows or other ranged weapons&mdash;only with bows and long bows.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Strength d8+, Shooting d10+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nslc8pagbdr","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"5u9JddXA4k9x55OO"}
{"name":"Death before Dishonor","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>This Edge is used only for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.ivGVp3v6VHZSNIYF]{Mass Battles}. The character has led his army to many victories, and the men have come to accept retreat as a stain on their honor.</p>\n<p>The character gains +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.9IwLt34etK096UAK]{Spirit} rolls when rolling for Morale in a Mass Battle.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Hold the Line, Spirit d8+, Battle d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_v523ge7encp","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Leadership Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"6CbxeHCA7FKIrXH2"}
{"name":"Natural Swimmer","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Your hero wasn't literally born in the water, but some might believe he was. He takes to it like a fish and can hold his breath longer than most others. Natural swimmers add +2 to their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.npGSR7Ru0Jl4LUXq]{Athletics} roll for Swimmings, add +1 to their Pace swimming, and can hold their breath 50% longer than others of their species.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: 50 Fathoms Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nth9juzzfye","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"6KX3BMOvFpOGOTSH"}
{"name":"Holy Adept","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Adepts are holy warriors who have trained themselves to be living weapons. Some do so to be ultimate warriors; others do it in the service of a cause or deity.</p>\n<p>Their unarmed attacks do @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.9IwLt34etK096UAK]{Strength}+d4 damage, and they are always considered armed for purposes of the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.FPyJrvPADnjDq6aD]{Unarmed Defender} rule.</p>\n<p>In addition, upon taking this Edge and at each new Rank, they may choose to change the trappings of one of the following powers to work only on themselves but be activated as a free action: @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.L4IbjoPtoc58262W]{Boost/Lower Trait}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.eBAobxB12YY1ifMn]{Deflection}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.nyShL2bXTxRwzBsN]{Healing}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.D0HgdnbWnDWxFWFf]{Smite}, or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.5BUeAC4BpmBnZjpn]{Speed}. The Adept must have the power to begin with, and this does not allow him to activate more than one power in a round.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Arcane Background (Miracles), Faith d8+, Fighting d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_04a7imn3lagw","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"6PqIJmnP45HVNQMB"}
{"name":"Femme Fatale/Ladykiller","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>The hero or heroine is a stunner, and knows how to get the best out of the opposite sex by using his or her charms.</p>\n<p>The character may use Persuasion as a Test of Will against members of the opposite sex, pitting their looks and charm against a foe's Smarts.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Lankhmar, City of Thieves</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Persuasion d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_04a7imn3lagw","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"6n86cfdtC6TLMwoh"}
{"name":"Cry Havoc!","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>This Edge is used only for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.ivGVp3v6VHZSNIYF]{Mass Battles}. The general has an uncanny knack for knowing when to unleash his troops and when to hold back.</p>\n<p>Once per battle, during the Battle Roll Phase, the character may declare a charge. He must do this before he or his opponent rolls their Battle die. If the character succeeds in his roll and beats his opponent, his enemy loses one extra token.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Fervor, Spirit d8+, Battle d10+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_v523ge7encp","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Leadership Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"73ny5E0OaHrBov46"}
{"name":"Brutal","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>The character with this @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.5r7x1AgEwLUihtZm]{edge} is more dangerous when roughed up. When determining melee damage, he adds his wound level to the roll. A hero with 3 wounds, for instance, adds +3 to his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.xCkOFlFmE1WwGXq6]{Fighting} damage rolls.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Lankhmar, City of Thieves</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Wild Card"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nslc8pagbdr","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"7gfIdxcGd4oErCsA"}
{"name":"Artifact Hunter","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Artifact Hunters scour ruins for magic items. If there is an Artifact Hunter in the party and you are using the rules for treasure found in the Fantasy Companion, the chance of finding a relic increases by 10%. If the chance is 100%, they find one artifact and have a 10% chance of finding a second.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Notice d10+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_04a7imn3lagw","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"8BoaZyeAjbyGsRVa"}
{"name":"Shieldwall","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>This Edge allows a hero to defend a comrade so long as the hero is using a medium or large shield.</p>\n<p>Attacks against one character adjacent to the hero suffer modifiers based on the hero's shield type. If there are multiple heroes with this Edge adjacent to a character or the target has his own shield, only the best modifier applies. A hero adjacent to multiple allies must declare which one he is protecting at the start of his turn.</p>\n<p>The hero also keeps his shield modifier if he is attacked.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Modified from Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Hobgoblin, Block, shield"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_rht8q8pjow","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"8igwzZCU8Eh3Ddim"}
{"name":"Favored Foe","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>The hero has a grudge against a specific race or type of creature, and has devoted time to learning how to best such creatures in combat.</p>\n<p>When this Edge is taken, the hero must pick one type of creature, such as orcs, dragons, giants, elementals, fey, undead, or demons. He has +1 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.1oRpVdlhWTK1fR5u]{Parry} against his favored foe, having learned how best to engage them in combat. He also rolls a d8 instead of a d6 if he scores a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.4FohNfzqnuY34ovd]{raise} on an attack roll against them.</p>\n<p>This Edge may be taken more than once, but the hero must choose a new foe each time he takes this Edge.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Smarts d8+, Fighting, Shooting, or Throwing d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nslc8pagbdr","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"8julnQCyHS8YkXJV"}
{"name":"Improved Focus","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Wielding arcane power has its drawbacks, but some people learn to keep their focus even when things don't go right.</p>\n<p>If a character with this Edge is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.5Qbb2JuTeN4XHgH5]{Shaken} as a result of failing to invoke a spell, he gets an immediate @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.9IwLt34etK096UAK]{Spirit} roll to recover.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic, Focus"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_pi4ivmcmcvb","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"94e4fu5Tp7MXJCNX"}
{"name":"Reactive Shifting","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Some shifters can activate their abilities as a reflex. Reactive Shifting allows them to begin shifting as a free action even when it's not their turn.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Shifter (any), Quick"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_rht8q8pjow","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"9649EIJyMejYjUrU"}
{"name":"Blind Fighting","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Blind fighters have trained long and hard to fight with out being able to see, using smell, sound, disturbances in the surrounding air, etc. You character is able to halves any penalties for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.xIvpccPze2BONfJA]{Illumination}.</p>\n<p>Note this edge does not allow you to see in the dark only to fight at a reduced penalty when you vision is impaired.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Legnds of Steel</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Agility d8+, Notice d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nslc8pagbdr","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"BOZ9shMzh0y3aJNy"}
{"name":"Siege Breaker","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>This Edge is used only for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.ivGVp3v6VHZSNIYF]{Mass Battles}. The hero has a good knowledge of siege warfare and can spot weaknesses in enemy fortifications.</p>\n<p>When he leads the army, the character reduces the Siege Bonus of any fortification his men are attacking by 1 (to a minimum of zero).</p>\n<p>If he makes a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.IHEg7dMezPJaIYsd]{Battle} roll at the start of a siege, he can increase the Siege Bonus penalty by an additional -1 for success and -2 with a raise by studying and exploiting specific weaknesses.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Command, Smarts d8+, Battle d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_v523ge7encp","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Leadership Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"BsXqZO5XSCLFUggO"}
{"name":"Steal Away","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>The hero uses distraction and cover to slip away from his foes.</p>\n<p>The character may make a single @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.bx5surfyOmSRgB1P]{Stealth} roll as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.E5UTH6Wqsi9DYlEN]{free action} to avoid attack when @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.SKOCsEd2ECoe2R92]{Withdrawing} from close combat. He suffers a -1 penalty for each adjacent foe. Failure means foes may attack as normal as the adventurer withdraws.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Rassilon Expansion II</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Agility d8+, Stealth d6+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nslc8pagbdr","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Ffo3lg0RNHQ1QEUl"}
{"name":"Drop!","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Once per round when a ranged weapon targets an ally within the hero's command radius, the character may order him to drop to the ground. This allows the intended target to fall @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.y3j8LVOAXinVVvh7]{prone} out of turn, even if he has acted already, gaining the benefits of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.bgwU76x12Ta7ntPK]{Medium Cover}.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Rassilon Expansion II</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Command, Notice d6+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_v523ge7encp","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Leadership Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"FhQFUlummUNxSSFa"}
{"name":"#[CF_tempEntity]","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"","range":"","rof":1,"ap":0,"minStr":"","shots":0,"currentShots":0},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nslc8pagbdr","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000","name":"Combat Edges","children":["XBQPoBQVpuhtkajb","BOZ9shMzh0y3aJNy","7gfIdxcGd4oErCsA","3sdEj0DW8JCA1QxO","x0UU8bG3g095WjqQ","YLJKqjokbwL4rXBs","8julnQCyHS8YkXJV","lpnmPlYzEKEuur2z","S7GOa0eiCtusuUx4","ip3ayHVWyQdFcDLA","xs0Jm8NQrvcydchj","dHRm4heV6A9gmjj4","5u9JddXA4k9x55OO","cs7fVm6gIsiDnJ5n","kpbjjOc3rhpN0Jga","Ffo3lg0RNHQ1QEUl","53lHBWQGKvV56UTA","mn2FC8oHqgZRMd7O","JpYnSCVAiL7pCrla","IhFORg1l071QXvK2","RuQJz62ARvAK65Bd"],"folderPath":["temp_oereppnkt5p"]}},"effects":[],"_id":"HSbSWqGxfL2mogu9"}
{"name":"Sunder","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Dwarves have an instinctual knowledge of materials. Those with this Edge know just where to strike objects or armored foes to cause the most damage. Any weapon in the hands of a dwarf with this Edge ignores 1 point of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.QyUeYxvX3yjnuH25]{armor} (in addition to any @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.wIG7zjXqXMDDKdiJ]{AP} value the weapon may already have) on a successful hit. If the dwarf gets a raise on the attack roll, he ignores 2 points of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.QyUeYxvX3yjnuH25]{armor}. The Edge applies against all forms of armor, natural or magical.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Dwarf"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_rht8q8pjow","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"IHdvwgaMaHn9LK2x"}
{"name":"True Hero","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>When lesser men fall by the wayside, this hero just keeps soldiering on.</p>\n<p>When the character takes enough wounds to make him Incapacitated, he may make a free @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.qy1LCq4m5ldlorDl]{Soak} roll. Should the roll fail, the hero may spend a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.LORAV4BtcI1ONG0C]{Benny} to make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.qy1LCq4m5ldlorDl]{Soak} roll as normal. If a character suffers multiple @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.5Qbb2JuTeN4XHgH5]{wounds} in the same round that take him to Incapacitated, he may make multiple free @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.qy1LCq4m5ldlorDl]{Soak} rolls.</p>\n<p class=\"embedded-example\"><strong>Example: </strong>Fafhrd already has 2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.5Qbb2JuTeN4XHgH5]{wounds}, when two vicious wolves sink their teeth into him, inflicting 2 and 3 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.5Qbb2JuTeN4XHgH5]{wounds} respectively. Fafhrd may make two free @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.qy1LCq4m5ldlorDl]{Soak} rolls, one against each attack.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Wild Card, Heroic, Iron Jaw"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nslc8pagbdr","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"IhFORg1l071QXvK2"}
{"name":"Attune Arcane Weapon","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Some artificers become adept at eking every advantage out of an arcane device's enchanted qualities.</p>\n<p>When wielding a weapon that is an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.UDWnUoqpSdpkWhsV]{arcane device}, artificers with this Edge gain a +1 bonus on attack and damage rolls. They must spend 24 hours with a newly acquired magic weapon before they can gain this benefit when wielding it.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Artificer"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_pi4ivmcmcvb","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"JABbl30ZGKlI8LSc"}
{"name":"True Berserker","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Some warriors nurture the rage inside them, learning to call upon it almost at will. A True Berserker may make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.9IwLt34etK096UAK]{Smarts} roll to activate his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.d0YwZF1Sf0cJgxJ4]{Berserk} Edge at any time.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Deadlands, Dark Ages</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Berserk, Spirit d6+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nslc8pagbdr","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"JpYnSCVAiL7pCrla"}
{"name":"Concentration","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Through training and focus, the caster is extremely efficient in channeling arcane forces. The caster can ignore up to 2 points of penalties on any power they cast.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Any), Smarts d6+, Spirit d6+, Vigor d6+"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_pi4ivmcmcvb","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"KnMG9jQAPK5vFCZL"}
{"name":"Imbue Item","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Artificers in Eberron understand and can manipulate magical energy in such a way that enables them to quickly imbue items and constructs, including living constructs, with infusions (powers imbued on objects). This allows her to use any @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.k4FQeOuzmYAhVaLF]{power} normally available to Artificers of her Rank or lower with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.ZUQ9fsJ5ybqBIByu]{Power Point} cost of 3 or lower and imbue any item with it.</p>\n<p>This takes one entire turn, during which she can do nothing else but make an Magecraft roll at -2 (she cannot take @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.On57BX9RxFSOBjzj]{Multi-Actions} that turn).</p>\n<p>The artificer uses @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.ZUQ9fsJ5ybqBIByu]{Power Points} directly from her pool for the device, but once its initial Duration is finished (it cannot be maintained) the item is not longer imbued.</p>\n<p><em>Renaming and modification of the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.IMhsK1VI9l31nCVB]{Gadgeteer} edge.</em></p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Modified from Savage Worlds Adventure Edition</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Magewright), Magecraft d6+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_pi4ivmcmcvb","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Koes1XdkqvTmg6vG"}
{"name":"Overload Metabolism","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>The warforged can heal damage at a cost to his other physical attributes by exciting his warforged metabolism. Once per session, he can make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.9IwLt34etK096UAK]{Vigor} roll to repair damage. On a success, he repairs one @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.5Qbb2JuTeN4XHgH5]{Wound}. On a raise, he repairs two @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.5Qbb2JuTeN4XHgH5]{Wounds}. Doing this reduces his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.9IwLt34etK096UAK]{Strength} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.9IwLt34etK096UAK]{Agility} by one die type for 10 minutes.</p>\n<p>If the warforged is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.5Qbb2JuTeN4XHgH5]{Incapacitated} and has not yet used this ability, any use of the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Imbue Item]{Imbue Item} Edge targeted upon him automatically activates this Edge.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Warforged, Agility d8+, Strength d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_rht8q8pjow","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"N0oMpjmM3UthfJs2"}
{"name":"Shifter Stamina","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Some shifters can persist with endurance beyond most others. Shifters with this Edge are immune to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.DT0J6tPSRkn517n8]{nonlethal damage}, and the effects of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.uQyy7EfJkaHAwXMp]{fatigue} are suppressed. When their shifting ends, any @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.uQyy7EfJkaHAwXMp]{fatigue} effects that would have taken effect during shifting (or that were in effect when shifting began) take effect normally.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Shifter (Beasthide, Truedive, or Wildhunt)"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_rht8q8pjow","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"N7je0oHWqyMqEClL"}
{"name":"University Trained","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>You attended one of the prestigious universities in the world. You like to read, and you absorb the information like a sponge. These books can be found in classrooms, in libraries or even in the local coffee shop. Book Learning confers 4 additional skill points on the Character, but these points must be spent on the following: <em>Arcana, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Battle]{Battle}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.fqYNzAjIQz8lKOBj]{★ Common Knowledge}, Cosmology, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Healing]{Healing}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Language]{Language}, Lore, Religion, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Research]{Research} </em>or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Science]{Science}.</p>\n<p>Because of your interest in books, a character with this Edge gains one additional Language at a d4.</p>\n<p><strong>Special: </strong>This Edge must be taken during character creation or after actually going to one of the schools of Khorvaire with DM approval.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nth9juzzfye","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"NY0rWJ5djDyEyRkc"}
{"name":"Bladedancer","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Bladedancers are elite elven warriors, this Edge is their trademark combat maneuver. Despite the name, they may use weapons.</p>\n<p>When used, an elf spins and dances about, attacking every opponent in his path like a deadly cyclone. On the tabletop, the character makes a running roll and must move that many inches. He may not double back.</p>\n<p>Every target adjacent to the fighter's path, starting with his initial position, is attacked at -2. One small downside to this Edge is that every adjacent target must be attacked&mdash;whether friend or foe. Individual targets may only be attacked once while using this Edge.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Elf, Agility d8+, Fighting d8+, Two-Fisted"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_rht8q8pjow","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"OBlie7l9MJlSkivY"}
{"name":"Explorer","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>There are two extremes of climate in the world, and this character has survived them both. He gains a +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Ai7tmypxa5M0DAuB]{Survival} rolls. in addition, he adds +2 to resist the effects of heat and cold related enviromental hazards.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Vigor d6+, Survival d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_04a7imn3lagw","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"P3crpqVF5NafypaQ"}
{"name":"Improved Scamper","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>The halfling can move so quickly as to cause multiple opponents to interfere with each other's attacks. Opponents get no @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.wryzn3CoavpCoTMq]{Ganging Up} bonus against the halfling.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Scamper"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_rht8q8pjow","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"PULJuaFBXiGN3aoj"}
{"name":"Knight","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Knights are chivalric heroes dedicated to a particular cause. All Knights swear holy oaths to their patron, whether it is a god, an order, or a noble, and must answer the call when summoned&mdash;even if it means his certain death.</p>\n<p>Upon acceptance into his order, a knight is gifted with the tools of his trade&mdash;a light warhorse, a lance, chain mail armor, and a medium shield emblazoned with the symbol of his patron.</p>\n<p>In addition to these material rewards, Knights of good causes gain +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.VrOjvkSpawKmH4go]{Persuasion}.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d6+, Strength d8+, Vigor d8+, Fighting d8+, Riding d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_04a7imn3lagw","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"QGgqRlx3tLqwOFxQ"}
{"name":"Wrestler","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>The hero is trained in holds, locks, and takedowns. She may roll @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.xCkOFlFmE1WwGXq6]{Fighting} instead of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.npGSR7Ru0Jl4LUXq]{Athletics} when @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.tTFnnG4CXI5DHaYE]{Grappling}. She may also roll @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.9IwLt34etK096UAK]{Strength}+d4 when @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.tTFnnG4CXI5DHaYE]{Crushing}. If she already has a damage die from @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.D4PPNUCqcUkCXwFo]{Claws}, the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.EecjbWEmGeRC1Yiq]{Martial Artist} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.VjaxBZIGjM80x3br]{Brawler} Edges, etc., increase the damage die by one type instead.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Fighting d6+, Agility or Strength d6+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nslc8pagbdr","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"RuQJz62ARvAK65Bd"}
{"name":"Improved Bilge Rat","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Scuttling around in the bowels of the ship doesn&rsquo;t suit every sailor, but this character has learned to adjust to the cramped conditions below deck.</p>\n<p>The character can use any weapon below decks without incurring the &ndash;2 penalty for fighting in cramped conditions.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: 50 Fathoms</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Bilge Rat"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nslc8pagbdr","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"S7GOa0eiCtusuUx4"}
{"name":"Entertainer","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>You character is skilled in ther performing arts: singing, story telling, comedy, acting, slieght of hand, etc. They also adept in speaking before a crowd.</p>\n<p>Pick any two of the following skills: @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.fqYNzAjIQz8lKOBj]{Common Knowledge}, Lore, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.LAPnQmjS9mpK7tzl]{Performance}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.VrOjvkSpawKmH4go]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Px53xqQ2nya4Pz6J]{Taunt}, or Traditions and add +1 to the total whenever they're used.</p>\n<p>This Edge may be taken more than once if applied to different skills.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Performance d6+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_04a7imn3lagw","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"SYzsQhna8rv9kK4m"}
{"name":"Tinkerer","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>On taking this Edge, the artificer may craft (or modify) an item that adds +1 to the user's relevant trait roll, increases the damage of a weapon by +1, or increases the bonus of armor by +1. No activation roll is required.</p>\n<p>Assuming the artificer is always \"fiddling\" with devices (not locked in prison, for example), and has adequate tools, he may make an Artificer roll at -4 at the end of any session in which he advances. If successful, he adds another +1 to any item of his choice.</p>\n<p>This could be his own wand (bonus to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.5hIUuseJglH1bUnz]{Shooting}), the clothing of another (bonus to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.QyUeYxvX3yjnuH25]{Armor}), or any other item of his choice. The item now adds that bonus to the user's relevant trait or damage roll, or armor rating. No item may have more than a +3 bonus.</p>\n<p><strong>Stacking:</strong> Bonuses from items don't stack, so a bow of accuracy +3 (@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.5hIUuseJglH1bUnz]{Shooting}) wielded by someone with targeting glasses +3 (@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.5hIUuseJglH1bUnz]{Shooting}) gets only the highest of the two.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Slipstream Player's Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Repair d8+, Magecraft d10+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_04a7imn3lagw","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"SdwB5knt87V24ew7"}
