{"name":"Psiforged Body","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>This warforged's body has trace amounts of psionically resonant deep crystal, providing her with increased psionic power and the ability to store psionic energy in its body. This functions as a mana stone (see Named Miscellaneous Magic in the Fantasy Companion) with 5 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.ZUQ9fsJ5ybqBIByu]{Power Points}. A warforged with this edge is sometimes referred to as a psiforged.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> This Edge must be taken during character creation.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Warforged, Arcane Background (Psionics)"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_rht8q8pjow","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"X9JNpLeyciVMeOaw"}
{"name":"Bilge Rat","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Scuttling around in the bowels of the ship doesn&rsquo;t suit every sailor, but this character has learned to adjust to the cramped conditions below deck.</p>\n<p>The character no longer suffers the &ndash;2 penalty when fighting below decks or in small quarters. If the weapon has a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.XfWDGAU17hRz00HV]{Reach}&nbsp;value the &ndash;2 penalty applies as normal.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: 50 Fathoms</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d8+, Fighting d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nslc8pagbdr","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"XBQPoBQVpuhtkajb"}
{"name":"Storm Chaser","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>When the weather is at its worst the character is at his best, seeming to read the storm like he would a book. Such characters are respected for their skill but feared for their love of a good storm.</p>\n<p>The character receives +1 to all @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.6U7wHNpFEuUSqLAs]{Boating} rolls made during a storm. In addition, the character may draw two cards during a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.jHMmYZHQJB7g0OkA]{Chases} each round during a storm and keep the best card, as long as he is the Captain. If the character has the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Wind Sense]{Wind Sense}&nbsp;Edge as well he draws three cards.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: 50 Fathoms</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Boating d8+ or Piloting d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_yuhzeq47stf","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Weird Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"XFrEiuzllUrAkVJu"}
{"name":"Arcane Background (Herbal Alchemy)","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><strong>Arcane Skill:</strong> Herbalism (Smarts)</p>\n<p><strong>Starting Powers: </strong>3</p>\n<p><strong>Power Points: </strong>Special</p>\n<p><strong>Powers Available: </strong><em>Arcane protection, beast friend, blast, blind, boost Trait</em> (not lower Trait)<em>, burst, conceal</em> (not detect)<em>, confusion, curse, darksight, disguise, empathy, entangle, enviromental protection, false health, farsight, fear, fly, growth/shrink, healing, intangibility, invisibility, jet, leaping, light/darkness, mind wipe, protection, pupppet, relief, shape change, sloth/speed. slumber, speak language, stun, telekinesis, wall walker, warrior's gift, zombie</em></p>\n<p><strong>Backlash: </strong>A Critical Failure on an Herbalism roll cases the Alchemist a level of Fatigue and all currently active powers are terminated. Optionally you may be called to roll on the Dynamic Backlash Table.</p>\n<p>Herbal alchemists are able to harvest ingredients from the natural environment--whether from flora or fauna--to create concoctions in the form of potions, poultices, ointments, edibles, and other alchemical products.</p>\n<h2>Herbal Alchemy Power Points</h2>\n<p>Herbal alchemists do not have their own reserve of Power Points like characters with other Arcane Backgrounds. Instead, they collect Power Points through components foraged using the Survival skill. Once per day, the herbal alchemist can make a Survival roll to forage for components. Each success and raise provides 5 Power Points worth of components. On a Critical Failure, the herbal alchemist somehow loses, ruins, or is forced to use components worth 1d4 Power Points. There is no limit to the amount of Power Points an herbal alchemist can collect over time.</p>\n<h2>Creating a Concoction</h2>\n<p>An herbal alchemist can spend 3 Power Points worth of components to create an individual concoction. This concoction must be a power whose effect, including modifiers and limitations, has a Power Point cost of 3 or lower. Creating a concoction takes one entire turn, during which the herbal alchemist can do nothing else but make an Herbalism roll to create the concoction. On failure, the concoction is ruined and the Power Points are lost. On a critical failure, the normal rules for Backlash apply. When the item is created, the effect is fixed, including the effects from a Raise on the Herbalism roll. Concoctions activate automatically when used. If a concoction requires a skill roll such as Athletics (Throwing) to use, the character must still roll that skill.</p>\n<h2>Power Edges</h2>\n<p>Of the Power Edges presented in the Savage Worlds core rules, this Arcane Background only satisfies the requirements for Channeling, Concentration, and New Powers.</p>\n<h2>Trappings</h2>\n<p>The trappings for herbal alchemy should center around potions, pultices, teas, herbal bags, etc.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Herbal Alchemy</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nth9juzzfye","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"XNLnKWtd80HhmNxO"}
{"name":"Improved Concentration","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Through training and focus, the caster is extremely efficient in channeling arcane forces. The caster is able to ignore up to 4 points of casting penatlies.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic, Concentration"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_pi4ivmcmcvb","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"XoHI0T214Ke0vfRj"}
{"name":"Fast Mount","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Mounting or dismounting a horse counts as an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.E5UTH6Wqsi9DYlEN]{action}. An adventurer with this edge can mount and dismount as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.E5UTH6Wqsi9DYlEN]{free action}, but may only perform one of each maneuver per round. Thus, the character could mount and dismount in one round, but he couldn't mount, dismount, and remount in the same round.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Rassilon Expansion II</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d8+, Riding d6+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nslc8pagbdr","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"YLJKqjokbwL4rXBs"}
{"name":"Arcane Background (Song Magic)","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><strong>Arcane Skill: </strong>Song Magic (Smarts)</p>\n<p><strong>Starting Powers: </strong>3</p>\n<p><strong>Power Points: </strong>10</p>\n<p><strong>Powers:</strong> <em>Analyze foe, arcane protection, banish, battle song, beast friend, boost/lower Trait, confusion, deflection, detect/conceal, disguise, dispel, elemental manipulation, false health, fear, gift of battle, illusion, legerdemain, message, puppet, relief,&nbsp; sloth/speed, slumber, sound/silence,&nbsp; speak language, stun, summon beast, ward, warrior's gift, whirlwind</em></p>\n<p><strong>Backlash: </strong>A Critical Failure on a song magic roll cases the skald a level of Fatigue and all currently active powers are terminated. Optionally you may be called to roll on the Dynamic Backlash Table.</p>\n<h2>Masters of Weaving Magic with Song</h2>\n<p>Song mages, more commonly known as bards or skalds, are magicians who work their magic through the power of song. The art is extremely ancient and found among all races, though the most skilled come from among House Phiarlin.</p>\n<p>As well as being spellcasters, bards and skalds are also storytellers and poets, able to recount epic poems and stories from memory. Some play instruments, but most simply use their voice to enthrall their audience. Their talents make them popular guests. Finding a warm place to sleep and a hot meal usually requires nothing more than a tale to entertain the host.</p>\n<p>A skald learns special techniques for memorizing things he has heard or read, and he is well versed in many topics. They have +1 to all Common Knowledge rolls, as well as Research rolls relating to riddles, history, folklore, and such like. Agility is used to play an instrument, bards being conversant in most forms.</p>\n<p>Bards and skalds are also popular with nobility and commoners alike and receive +1 Persuasion rolls.</p>\n<h2>Casting</h2>\n<p>Bards and Skalds must be able to speak to work their magic, but don't need to use their hands. Once the spell is cast, the skald may stop singing, even if the spell is to be Maintained.</p>\n<h2>Trappings</h2>\n<p>The trappings for Song Magic would include singing or playing an instrument. One should consider naming their spells based off the name of a song or poem pointing towards the type of power.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nth9juzzfye","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"YTHy8F3gmnmr1Uei"}
{"name":"Legendary Storyteller","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>The party gains +1d8 Glory for each raise after the first when using the Variable Glory Awards.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic, Master Storyteller"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_04a7imn3lagw","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"YxvX84oLfoOOLW9A"}
{"name":"Arcane Background (Dragonmark)","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><strong>Arcane Skill:</strong> Dragonmark Focus (Spirit)</p>\n<p><strong>Starting Powers: </strong>1</p>\n<p><strong>Power Points: </strong>15</p>\n<p><strong>Available Powers: </strong>Based on dragonmark, see Dragonmark Abilities and Powers below.</p>\n<p><strong>Backlash: </strong>A Critical Failure on a Dragonmark Focus roll causes the Dragonmarked Heir a level of Fatigue and all currently active powers are terminated. Optionally you may be called to roll on the DragonMark Backlash Table.</p>\n<p><strong>Race and Aberrrant Dragonmarks: </strong>This Arcane Background is only available to dragonmarked races. Races with multiple choices can only ever choose to have one kind of dragonmark. Adventurers with an Aberrant Dragonmark cannot select this Arcane Background as well.</p>\n<p><strong>Rank: </strong>Rank requirements for the Power are ignored when taking this edge.</p>\n<p><strong>Skill Bonus:</strong> The mark also grants a +1 bonus to one skill. Each should be chosen from the options listed along side the dragonmark that manifests.</p>\n<h2>Dragonmarked Heir</h2>\n<p>The adventurer has a dragonmark as appropriate to his race, and is considered a dragonmarked heir. The dragonmark grants the a power from those available to the a particular Mark. In addition a bonus to one skill used by heirs of that dragonmark. The dragonmark grants the ability to use dragonmark focus items and a power granted by that specific mark.</p>\n<p>Each time the adventurer selects the New Power or Power Points Edge for this Arcane Background, the dragonmark changes into a larger, more complex pattern and increases in power.</p>\n<h2>Dragonmark Appearance</h2>\n<p>A dragonmark appears on the skin. There are twelve known dragonmarks, each unique in design and power. A dragonmark can appear on any part of the body. One half-elf could have the Mark of Detection across an eye, while another has it in the palm of the hand. Dragonmarks appear with vivid shades of blue and purple and shimmer or even move slightly.</p>\n<h2>Dragonmarks and Backgrounds</h2>\n<p>Dragonmarks are bound to certain bloodlines, and by choosing a mark, you are establishing your character's blood connection to one of the families in the dragonmarked houses. It's up to you to define your relationship to the house. Were you brought up in the house? Or are you independent from it? This is best represented by your background. Consider the following options:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Agent.</strong> You have a close, ongoing relationship with your house. The house agent background is a good choice if you are actively working for the house. Alternately, you could take the noble background to reflect a blood tie to the leaders of the house.</li>\n<li><strong>Independent Scion. </strong>You were raised or trained by the house, but you've kept your independence. This means you don't have many special privileges, but you also don't have responsibilities. Guild artisan is a good choice to reflect basic house training, but you could choose entertainer for the Mark of Shadow, sailor for the Mark of Storms, soldier for the Mark of Sentinel, sage for the Mark of Scribing, and so on.</li>\n<li><strong>Excoriate. </strong>When a dragonmarked heir defies their house, they might be cut off from their family. In the past, your mark would be flayed from your body. Although this mutilation is no longer practiced, such exiles are still called excoriates. If you're an excoriate, consider what you did to deserve this punishment. Were you a criminal? A charlatan? Or perhaps a sage who engaged in forbidden research?</li>\n<li><strong>Foundling. </strong>Your ancestors left the house long ago. You have no ties to the house and may not have known you were connected by blood before you manifested your dragonmark. As an outlander or an urchin, you might know nothing about the houses. As an acolyte or a hermit, you could have put your faith ahead of worldly things, choosing not to pursue a connection with the houses. Whatever you decide, this is an opportunity to talk with your DM about the role you'd like the house to play in a campaign. Do you want them to be your enemy? Would you prefer to avoid them completely? Or do you want to work your way into a position of power in the house, despite being an outsider?</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Trappings</h2>\n<p>All dragonmark powers, come from the dragonmark themselves and therefore tend to be subtle. Trappings would generally be the dragonmark growing warm to the touch and producing a soft glow. Other types of trappings can be created that should follow along these lines.</p>\n<p><strong>Hands Free:</strong> The bearer of a dragonmark does not need thier hands free to be able to cast their dragonmark power(s).</p>\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Dragonmark Abilities and Powers</h2>\n</caption>\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Mark</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Race</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill Bonus</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Powers</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Mark of Detection</td>\n<td>Half-elf</td>\n<td>+1 to Notice or Netowrking (Both Persuasion and Intimidation, see Savage Worlds core rules)</td>\n<td><em>Boost Vigor, darksight, detect/conceal, divination, enviromental protection</em></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Mark of Finding</td>\n<td>Half-orc, human, or orc</td>\n<td>+1 to Notice or Survival</td>\n<td><em>Analyze foe, detect, farsight, insight, object reading</em></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Mark of Handling</td>\n<td>Human</td>\n<td>+1 to Animal Handling or Riding rolls</td>\n<td><em>Beast friend, boost Trait (</em>animals only<em>), empathy (</em>animals only<em>), summon beast</em></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Mark of Healing</td>\n<td>Halfling</td>\n<td>+1 to Healing or Survival rolls</td>\n<td>Accelerate healing, boost Vigor, false health, healing, relief</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Mark of Hospitality</td>\n<td>Halfling</td>\n<td>+1 to Common KNowledge or Persuasion rolls</td>\n<td><em>Create food and drink, dimensional space, empathy (</em>humanoids only<em>), elemental manipulation (</em>air, fire and water only<em>)</em></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Mark of Making</td>\n<td>Human</td>\n<td>+1 to Crafting or Repair rolls</td>\n<td><em>Creation, drain power points (</em>arcane devices only<em>), magecraft, repairing</em></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Mark of Passage</td>\n<td>Human</td>\n<td>+1 to Piloting or Riding rolls</td>\n<td><em>Dimensional space, speed, summon beast (</em>mount only<em>), teleport</em></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Mark of Scribing</td>\n<td>Gnome</td>\n<td>+1 to Lore and Research rolls</td>\n<td><em>Magic mark, message, secret writing, speak language</em></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Mark of Sentinel</td>\n<td>Human</td>\n<td>+1 to Battle, Fighting, or Shooting rolls</td>\n<td><em>Boost Trait, deflection, gift of battle, protection,&nbsp; warrior's gift</em></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Mark of Shadow</td>\n<td>Elf</td>\n<td>+1 to performance or Stealth rolls</td>\n<td><em>Darkness, disguise, illusion, intangibility, legerdem ain</em></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Mark of Storm</td>\n<td>Half-elf</td>\n<td>+1 to Boating or Piloting rolls</td>\n<td><em>Becalm, elemental manipulation (</em>air and water only<em>), tempest, whirlwind, zephyr</em></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Mark of Warding</td>\n<td>Dwarf</td>\n<td>+1 to Notice or Thievery rolls</td>\n<td><em>Arcane protection, barrier glyph, lock/unlock, sentry, ward</em></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Dragonmarked Race"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nth9juzzfye","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ZOoUAEvz3bGkeW6k"}
{"name":"Siege Mentality","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>This Edge is used only for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.ivGVp3v6VHZSNIYF]{Mass Battles}. The character has a strong defensive mentality and understands how to make the most of his fortification and its defenders.</p>\n<p>When he leads the army, he increases the Siege Bonus of any fortification he defends by +1.</p>\n<p>If he makes a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.IHEg7dMezPJaIYsd]{Battle} roll at the start of a siege, he can increase this bonus by an additional +1 for success and +2 with a raise by studying and better defending weak areas.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Command, Smarts d8+, Battle d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_v523ge7encp","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Leadership Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ZpmUkRVYMSuebfA3"}
{"name":"Arcane Background (Druidism)","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><strong>Arcane Skill: </strong>Druidism (Spirit)</p>\n<p><strong>Starting Powers: </strong>3</p>\n<p><strong>Power Points: </strong>10</p>\n<p><strong>Powers: </strong><em>Accelerate healing, animate war tree, arcane protection, banish, barrier, beast friend, becalm, blast, blind, bolt, boost/lowerTrait, burrow, burst, confusion, create food and drink, detect/conceal, elemental manipulation, empathy </em>(animals only)<em>, entangle, enviromental protection, fly, growth </em>(NOT shirnk)<em>, havoc, healing, jet</em><em>, message </em>(animals only)<em>, mind link </em>(animals only)<em>, mind reading </em>(animals only),<em> protection, puppet, relief, resurrection, sentry, shape change, smite, summon beast, tempest, wall walker, zephyr&nbsp;</em></p>\n<p><strong>Backlash:</strong> A Critical Failure on a druidism roll cases the druid a level of Fatigue and all currently active powers are terminated. Optionally you may be called to roll on the Dynamic Backlash Table.</p>\n<p><strong>Activation: </strong>Druids must be able to speak and gesture (they cannot be Bound as per the Savage Worlds core rules) to cast their spells.</p>\n<p><strong>Environments: </strong>Modifiers apply to Druidism rolls based on the environment in which they are using their powers. While druids are typically powerful in natural environments, they suffer penalties while within artificial or worked structures which block the natural magic flowing within the Dragon Between.</p>\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Druidism Casting Enviroments</h2>\n</caption>\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Modifier</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Enviroment</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>+1</td>\n<td>In the wild</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>+0</td>\n<td>Rural (farm, worked cavern, mine)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>-1</td>\n<td>Urban (town or city, artificial structures)<br /><br /></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h2>One with Nature</h2>\n<p>The fury of a storm, the gentle strength of the morning sun, the cunning of the fox, the power of the bear&mdash;all these and more are at the druid&rsquo;s command. The druid however, claims no mastery over nature. That claim, she says, is the empty boast of a city dweller. The druid gains her power not by ruling nature but by being at one with it. To trespassers in a druid&rsquo;s sacred grove, and to those who feel her wrath, the distinction is overly fine.</p>\n<p>Druids draw their power from the natural energy fields surrounding the earth, plants, and animals. Although they do manipulate the elemental energy fields, their skill is limited. A druid reveres nature above all. She gains her magical power either from the force of nature itself or from a nature deity. The typical druid pursues a mystic spirituality of transcendent union with nature rather than devoting herself to a divine entity.</p>\n<h2>Trappings</h2>\n<p>Since Druids draw their power from the natural energy fields surrounding the earth, plants, and animals, the trappings of their powers should come from that very natural source. Grasping vines, union with the trees, swarms of insects, birds flocking are all kinds of trappings that should manifest for the powers of Druids.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nth9juzzfye","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"bBwDM4fIwya3waIl"}
{"name":"Healing Factor","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>After the shifter's current period of shifting ends, she may immediately make a free @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.qy1LCq4m5ldlorDl]{Soak} roll to remove any @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.5Qbb2JuTeN4XHgH5]{Wounds} taken while shifted.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Shifter (any), Vigor d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_rht8q8pjow","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"crtDogJlWYNxSx5i"}
{"name":"Mounted Combatant","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>The character has a knack for getting the best out of his mount.</p>\n<p>They ignore two points of penalties to any @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.GbtBgL3WJNN3SBlm]{Riding} roll, and may spend @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.LORAV4BtcI1ONG0C]{Bennies} to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.qy1LCq4m5ldlorDl]{Soak} damage for any mount they are riding or command, using the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.GbtBgL3WJNN3SBlm]{Riding} skill instead of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.9IwLt34etK096UAK]{Vigor}. Each success and raise negates a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.5Qbb2JuTeN4XHgH5]{Wound}.</p>\n<p>Furthermore, he may make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.GbtBgL3WJNN3SBlm]{Riding} roll as an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.E5UTH6Wqsi9DYlEN]{action} to spur his mount to greater speeds. With success, the mount gains +2 Pace for this round. a failure causes the mount to gain no increase to its Pace and it suffers a level of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.uQyy7EfJkaHAwXMp]{Fatigue} due to the exertion.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Rassilon Expansion II</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Riding d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nslc8pagbdr","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"cs7fVm6gIsiDnJ5n"}
{"name":"Lunge","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>A lunge allows a swordsman to extend the reach of his weapon. The character gains +1 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.XfWDGAU17hRz00HV]{Reach} to his weapon. He may not use this Edge with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.R0tfd1gh2HarRjsa]{First Strike}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.XcO1OKzJmCozkpTJ]{Frenzy}, or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.5TWI3a1ZN23CpcVL]{Sweep}.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Lankhmar, City of Thieves</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Fighting d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nslc8pagbdr","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"dHRm4heV6A9gmjj4"}
{"name":"Necromancer","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Necromancers are steeped in the lore and rituals of death. They are particularly adept at raising the dead and forcing them to serve their foul requests. While most heroes should avoid such vile sorcery, few can deny its efficiency.</p>\n<p>The benefits of the Necromancer Edge are two-fold. First, the Necromancer may cast the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.r0th5J4i4Kr4DXQH]{Zombie} power at @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.DmjoeV2Yi7z3iGiw]{Novice} level (rather than its normal @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.DmjoeV2Yi7z3iGiw]{Veteran} Rank requirement).</p>\n<p>Second, when casting zombie , the Necromancer reduces the Power Point cost to 2/corpse. Additionally, he may double the cost per corpse to increase the Duration to 2d6 hours with a success, 2d6 days with a raise, or permanent with two raises.</p>\n<p>A Necromancer may never have more than twice his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.9IwLt34etK096UAK]{Spirit} die in permanent undead servants.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Horror Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Arcane Background (Magic or Miracles), Spirit d8+, arcane skill d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_04a7imn3lagw","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"fZSKCWquGBan2JDQ"}
{"name":"Improved Enchant","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Improved Enchant works the same way as @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Enchant]{Enchant} with one important exception--the power is \"always on\" and no longer requires @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.ZUQ9fsJ5ybqBIByu]{Power Points} to use (it has infinite points). The cost, however, is 1000 galifars of Eberron Dragonshards per @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.ZUQ9fsJ5ybqBIByu]{Power Point} required to activate the power.</p>\n<p class=\"embedded-example\"><strong>Example: </strong>Enchanting a sword with Smite would require 2000 galifars of Eberron Dragonshards.</p>\n<p>When the device is created, the creator makes an arcane skill roll. Failure means the Eberron Dragonshards are lost (and at the GM's fiat, the device is destroyed as well--or it could become cursed). A success means the power is activated as usual. A raise means the power forever activates with a raise (if desired by the user).</p>\n<p>Artifacts which are always on (a ring of invisibility, a cloak of stealth, and so on), don't require an arcane skill roll to activate&mdash;but may require an action to \"ready\"&mdash;the ring must be put on, the cloak pulled over the shoulder, etc. Thus a ring of invisibility could always be worn and require no activation roll&mdash;but the wearer would always be invisible.</p>\n<p>Artifacts requiring activation, such as a wand of fireballs, require a suitable skill roll (Shooting for wands, for example). All artifacts created using this Edge are called major artifacts.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Gear Toolkit</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Legendary, Enchat"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_jplxnelbxxe","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Legendary Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"fw2AnfnY90xeR0m1"}
{"name":"Master Artificer","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Truly experienced artificers can inscribe runes of power that provide an item with an Edge. This Edge uses the same rules as @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Adept Artificer]{Adept Artificer}, with two notable exception. While the character need not have the Edge he is placing into an item, he must be of the same rank. For instance, a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.DmjoeV2Yi7z3iGiw]{Seasoned} character could not inscribe Improved @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.R0tfd1gh2HarRjsa]{First Strike}. Secondly with this more powerful magic, at least 1000 galifars of Eberron Dragonshards are required for the imbueing.</p>\n<p>An individual item may contain no more than three Edges (again, items with more are considered true relics and beyond the ken of characters). Where an Edge requires another Edge as a requirement (such as @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.X5GStACnzpvOqLY2]{Improved Frenzy} needing @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.XcO1OKzJmCozkpTJ]{Frenzy}), the requirement Edge must be worked into the item first and uses one of the item's two Edge \"slots.\"</p>\n<p>Edges placed in items allow anyone wearing or carrying the object (as appropriate) to gain the benefits of the Edge without needing to meet the requirements.</p>\n<p>An item must be worn or a weapon drawn to gain the effects of the Edge. Simply owning an axe of the berserker does not grant one the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.d0YwZF1Sf0cJgxJ4]{Berserk} Edge.</p>\n<p><strong>Stacking: </strong>Some Edges, typically those granting a fixed bonus, do stack with Edges possessed by the wielder.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Gear Toolkit</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Adept Artificer"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_pi4ivmcmcvb","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"gTSe9hZWkpnWPGLV"}
{"name":"Arcane Background (Wand Magic)","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><strong>Arcane Skill: </strong>Wand Magic (Smarts)</p>\n<p><strong>Starting Powers: </strong>3</p>\n<p><strong>Power Points: </strong>15</p>\n<p><strong>Available Powers: </strong><em>Arcane protection, blind, bolt, lower Trait ( not boost Trait), burst, confusion, darksight, detect</em> ( not <em>conceal</em>)<em>, elemental manipulation, entangle, fear, havoc, jet, light/darkness, relief, silence, smite, sound/silence, stun, barrier, blast, curse, dispel, shrink </em>( not <em>growth</em>)<em>, sloth, slumber, telekinesis, whirlwind, accelerate healing, drain power points, glyph, puppet, tempest</em></p>\n<p><strong>Backlash: </strong>A Critical Failure on a Wand Magic roll causes the Wand Adept a level of Fatigue and all currently active powers are terminated. Optionally you may be called to roll on the Wand Magic Backlash table.</p>\n<h2>Rise of the Wand Adept</h2>\n<p>Wandslingers channel arcane firepower energy through the arcane foci of wands, staffs, or rods. Wandslingers came to the fore during the Last War, with Aundair fielding the largest number. Using the arcane focus and channeling arcane power, required less training than other traditional forms of magic. However it allowed a bit more power to be focused using the wand, staff or rod.</p>\n<h2>Increased Power Modifiers</h2>\n<p><strong>Wands:</strong> When the wandslinger uses a wand they are able to use the Range (double range only) or Selective power modifier without spending any additional Power Points. Only one power modifer can be added per casting.</p>\n<p><strong>Rod:</strong> When using a Rod the wandslinger can add the Range (double or triple), Selective, Glow, Hinder, Lingering Damage, or Fatigue power modifier without spending any additional Power Points. Two +1 power modifiers can be cast at once, or one +2 power modifier.</p>\n<p><strong>Staff: </strong>When using a Staff the wandslinger can add the Range (double or triple), Selective, Glow, Hinder, Armor Piercing, Heavy Weapon, Lingering Damage, or Fatigue power modifier without spending any additional Power Points. Any combination of up to +3 power modifiers can be cast at once.</p>\n<h2>Trappings</h2>\n<p>Wand adepts' arcane powers take the form of wand, rods, and staves. Trappings for powers cast should be instilled in one of those devices.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nth9juzzfye","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"gn4HeWXp8YNwP65B"}
{"name":"#[CF_tempEntity]","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"","range":"","rof":1,"ap":0,"minStr":"","shots":0,"currentShots":0},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_fn2ree8y25p","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Social Edges","color":"#000000","name":"Social Edges","children":["pf08yjEsFI0r8Mps"],"folderPath":["temp_oereppnkt5p"]}},"effects":[],"_id":"h5zvdnIsNv6igVsb"}
{"name":"Improved Close Fighting","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Close fighters train to go for vital areas and weak spots for quick and lethal kills. The attacker adds +1 to his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.xCkOFlFmE1WwGXq6]{Fighting} roll equal to his enemy's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.XfWDGAU17hRz00HV]{Reach} +1.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Lankhmar, City of Thieves</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Close Fighting"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nslc8pagbdr","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ip3ayHVWyQdFcDLA"}
{"name":"Extra Shifter Ability","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>The adventurer come from a mixed lineage of shifters and has one additional shifter ability. They can manifest this additional ability while shifted as well.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Shifter (any)"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_rht8q8pjow","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"jCdzwXrTur4O1MPh"}
{"name":"House Scion","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>This individual was born into the privilege of a dragonmarked house or came into it later in life. She may or may not have money (the Rich or Filthy Rich Edge), but she still walks in the elite circles of the dragonmarked houses.</p>\n<p>This character will likely be able to take on the name of their house for a last name, denoting being a scion of the house.</p>\n<p>House scions add +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.VrOjvkSpawKmH4go]{Persuasion} when @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Networking]{Networking} with other house members. They also add +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.fqYNzAjIQz8lKOBj]{Common Knowledge} rolls made to know the information about what is going on within their house, recognize family names or members of their house, or recall gossip concerning others within their house.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nth9juzzfye","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"jrjtQewN5V05tHCV"}
{"name":"Improved Primal Fury","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>With sufficient willpower, a hero who has learned to trigger his rage can restrain it as well. Improved Primal Fury allows the hero to ignore the -2 penalty to end his rage, and on a roll of 1 on his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.xCkOFlFmE1WwGXq6]{Fighting} die, he will not hit an ally while @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.d0YwZF1Sf0cJgxJ4]{Berserk} (though he may still hit the wrong opponent or miss).</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Primal Fury, Spirit d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_rht8q8pjow","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"kJG6T39S5QNZ3P9T"}
{"name":"Oversized Weapon Master","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>The character may use @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.TopFsh8yBIVN5QWe]{two-handed} melee weapons with one hand. He may only use one such weapon at a time, even if he has the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Joxt7yxKX7aUdxeQ]{Ambidextrous} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.cworAb5mmtNzuxwD]{Two-Fisted} Edges, though he may use an oversize weapon in this manner and wield a standard one-handed weapon simultaneously.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player's Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Strength d10+, Fighting d10+, Size 0 or greater"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nslc8pagbdr","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"kpbjjOc3rhpN0Jga"}
{"name":"Monster Hunter","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>The character is completely immune to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.VEsADnXDGeBjc54c]{Fear} checks from one broad type of creature, such as ghosts, werewolves, vampires, or constructs. If applied to spellcasters, it includes the fear spell as well.</p>\n<p>The Game Master is the final arbiter of whether or not the Edge applies to a particular horror.</p>\n<p>The Edge may be taken multiple times, each applying to a different creature type.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Horror Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Spirit d6+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_04a7imn3lagw","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"lBNuUvHdMMeGz0n8"}
{"name":"Ground Fighter","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>The hero does not suffer @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.1oRpVdlhWTK1fR5u]{Parry} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.xCkOFlFmE1WwGXq6]{Fighting} roll reductions when @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.y3j8LVOAXinVVvh7]{prone}. If engaged in melee against an opponent who is also @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.y3j8LVOAXinVVvh7]{prone}, the hero adds +1 to his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.npGSR7Ru0Jl4LUXq]{Athletics} (if @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.tTFnnG4CXI5DHaYE]{Grappling}) or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.xCkOFlFmE1WwGXq6]{Fighting} rolls.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility or Strength d6+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nslc8pagbdr","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"lpnmPlYzEKEuur2z"}
{"name":"Symbiont Mastery","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>The adventurer has stronger control over attached symbionts and benefits from increased vitality from the attached symbionts. She gains a +2 bonus to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.9IwLt34etK096UAK]{Spirit} rolls during any battle of wills between her and the symbiont (see Intelligent Relics in Fantasy Companion). While at least one symbiont is attached, the adventurer also gains a free reroll on @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.5Qbb2JuTeN4XHgH5]{Soak} rolls.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d6+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_yuhzeq47stf","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Weird Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"mRlUe9x35X34BB5b"}
{"name":"Takedown Move","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>When the hero successfully @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.EBCnv0jdi45eCy1c]{Pushes} an opponent, the opponent must make an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.npGSR7Ru0Jl4LUXq]{Athletics} roll at -2 (-4 if the hero got a raise) or be knocked @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.y3j8LVOAXinVVvh7]{prone}.</p>\n<p>The wrestler can also chose not to push the opponent 1\" away, but just @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.y3j8LVOAXinVVvh7]{prone}.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Wrestler"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nslc8pagbdr","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"mn2FC8oHqgZRMd7O"}
{"name":"A Few Good Men","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>This Edge is used only for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.ivGVp3v6VHZSNIYF]{Mass Battles}. The character knows how to get the best from the troops at his disposal.</p>\n<p>Once the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.ivGVp3v6VHZSNIYF]{tokens} for each force have been calculated, the character adds one token to his army's total to account for their status.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic, Inspire, Smarts d8+, Battle d10+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_v523ge7encp","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Leadership Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"oKBAaCR206BdtC3B"}
{"name":"Honey Tongue","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Whether a master merchant, talented courtesan, or flirtatious fence, this character is a master of flattery, innuendo, and fabrications. The character's ability to confuse and distract allows him to make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.XbY9qh8iHoDcbM5c]{Tests} using @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.VrOjvkSpawKmH4go]{Persuasion} opposed by the target's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.9IwLt34etK096UAK]{Smarts}, instead of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.9IwLt34etK096UAK]{Spirit}.</p>\n<p>Additionally, this smooth talker is an expert negotiator. When selling goods he is able to unload the items at 60% the price with a successful @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.VrOjvkSpawKmH4go]{Persuasion} roll, or at 75% value with a raise.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Lankhmar, City of Thieves</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d6+, Spirit d6+, Persuasion d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_fn2ree8y25p","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Social Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"pf08yjEsFI0r8Mps"}
{"name":"Wind Sense","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>The character has an almost supernatural knowledge of air and wind. He can sense changes in the weather and wind direction long before they actually happen.</p>\n<p>If the character is piloting a ship he gains +1 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.6U7wHNpFEuUSqLAs]{Boating} rolls during Contact, using his knowledge of the winds to outrun and catch prey.</p>\n<p>In addition, the character may draw two cards during a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.jHMmYZHQJB7g0OkA]{Chase} each round during a storm and keeps the best as long as the Captain heeds his warnings. If the character has the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Storm Chaser]{Storm Chaser} Edge as well he draws three cards.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: 50 Fathoms</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d8+, Boating d8+ or Piloting d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_yuhzeq47stf","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Weird Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"phOgZZTXELUps6zh"}
{"name":"War Cry","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Bugbear, Half-orc, and Orc can bellow an ear-splitting, nervewracking war cry that has been known to send lesser foes fleeing from the field.</p>\n<p>When used, the character may make an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Cd3SxYtdga0JdnV0]{Intimidation} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.XbY9qh8iHoDcbM5c]{test} against all targets in an area (as opposed to a single victim as usual). Place the edge of a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.VQvyYBQG9Gh4VdWa]{Large Blast Template} adjacent to the character. Every creature, friend and foe, within the circle must roll against the hero's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Cd3SxYtdga0JdnV0]{Intimidation} total.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Bugbear, Half-orc, or Orc, Intimidation d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_rht8q8pjow","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"pnDzbTWPPI0yrqpo"}
{"name":"Adept Artificer","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Adept Artificers may not have the ability to create true relics but after they have mastered imbuing powers into arcane devices, she can advance to crafting more permanent magic items. Artificers with this Edge have the ability to make minor artifacts.</p>\n<p>Runes are the most common \"trapping\" of this Edge, but such details are left to the individual artificer.</p>\n<p>On taking this Edge, the hero may craft (or modify) an item that adds +1 to the one trait roll, increases the damage of a weapon by +1, or increases the bonus of armor by +1. No activation roll is required.</p>\n<p>Only items that were crafted with a Raise have enough quality to be magically imbued with this kind of power.</p>\n<p>Assuming the artificer is always \"fiddling\" with devices (not locked in a dungeon, for example), has adequate tools, and uses 250 galfiars worth of Eberron Dragonshards, he may make as Arcana roll at -4 at the end of any session in which he advances. If successful, he adds another +1 to any item of his choice.</p>\n<p>This could be his own blade, the cloak of another, or any other item of his choice. The item now adds that bonus to the user's relevant trait or damage roll, or armor rating. No item may have more than a +2 total bonuses (such devices are relics and outside the scope of this ability). The bonuses need not apply to the same trait.</p>\n<p><strong>Stacking:</strong> Bonuses from items don't stack, so a sword +3 (Fighting) wielded by someone with gauntlets +3 (Fighting) gets only the highest of the two.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Gear Toolkit</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Artificer, Arcane Background (Dragonmark of Making, Magic, Magecraft, or Miracles), Arcana d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_pi4ivmcmcvb","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"qMGAMviJPhElEPSC"}
{"name":"Guardian","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>This character might be a professional bodyguard or just intensely devoted, but in either case he can jump in front of attacks intended for another. A character with this Edge must declare whom he is guarding at the beginning of any combat. As long as the guardian stays within 1\" of the chosen person, any attack aimed at that person is automatically rolled against the guardian instead. A guardian can switch charges during a battle, but doing so requires an action as the guardian re-focuses his attention.</p>\n<p>The character receives a benny each time he takes a Wound (not Shaken) while defending another character (Extra or Wild Card) during a specific encounter.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Slipstream Player's Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d8+, Fighting d6+, Notice d6+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_04a7imn3lagw","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"qX9oQqYXFz9nPuYM"}
{"name":"Artificer","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Those who tangle with supernatural forces sometimes find ways to imbue powers into items. They may turn an ordinary blade into a magic sword, grant powerful potions to their friends, or even bless holy relics with divine grace.</p>\n<p>The artificer can create <strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.UDWnUoqpSdpkWhsV]{Arcane Devices}&nbsp;</strong>and give them to their allies.</p>\n<p>Consumable items such as potions or herbal remedies require the arcane skill roll upon creation rather than at the time of use. The creator knows immediately whether her arcane skill roll succeeded or failed.</p>\n<p>Players should use common sense when creating Arcane Devices . For instance, <em>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.TbcqRtdavoGl7niL]{Bolt}</em> makes more sense in a wand rather than an oil. <em>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.jNbTbrOAKFDgVPOq]{Obscure}</em> could be a potion, but would be thrown or sprinkled over an area rather than drunk. The GM has the final say on whether a spell belongs in a potion, scroll, or other object.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Modified from Savage Worlds Adventure Edition</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Any)"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_pi4ivmcmcvb","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"quNu9hNtLdyQDAML"}
{"name":"Adamantine Body","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>The warforged was created from a specially designed line made with adamantine giving him +4 Armor instead of the normal +2 from Composite Plating.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> This Edge must be taken during character creation.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Warforged"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_rht8q8pjow","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"qxF5SHd39R7ox6t6"}
{"name":"Boarder","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Many captains instill courage in their men by offering additional rewards to the first man to board an enemy vessel. Few survive to claim their prize. Through skill and luck the character has survived dozens of boarding actions and feels empowered by the adrenaline rush.</p>\n<p>All @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.npGSR7Ru0Jl4LUXq]{Athletics} rolls involving ropes are made at +2. Anytime he is the first allied character to board an enemy vessel he receives a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.LORAV4BtcI1ONG0C]{Benny}.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: 50 Fathoms</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Boating d6+, Athletics d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_04a7imn3lagw","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"r38DPA6TWDm3i26g"}
{"name":"Coordinated Firepower","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>The hero knows how to coordinate missile fire against a single foe.</p>\n<p>Instead of firing separately, all missile troops within the hero's command radius yet to act in the round can fire as a single unit on the hero's action (this counts as their entire action for the round).</p>\n<p>The hero nominates one foe within range of his weapon. He then makes a single @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.npGSR7Ru0Jl4LUXq]{Athletics} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.5hIUuseJglH1bUnz]{Shooting} roll, as appropriate for his weapon. Each additional missile soldier within the hero's command radius (and within range of the target), firing at the same time adds a flat +2 to the attack roll.</p>\n<p>Damage is calculated as normal for the hero's weapon, but he adds +1d6 per raise (not just for the first raise). Coordinating fire in this manner counts as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.E5UTH6Wqsi9DYlEN]{single action}.</p>\n<p>A hero cannot use Double Shot or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.mUgnvgGhyCRc5nQ7]{Giant Killer} in conjunction with this Edge unless all subordinates firing with the hero have those Edges as well.</p>\n<p>Although the soldiers lose their individual attacks, the combined firepower gives a better chance of bringing down a large foe (like a dragon), and unlike separate missile fire, the entire damage roll is applied once against the foe's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.cJyRxOTlGTYzyf15]{Toughness}.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Command, Smarts d6+, Shooting d8+ or Athletics d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_v523ge7encp","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Leadership Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"rSZWzcaIwpErQZGA"}
{"name":"Escape Artist","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Ropes, chains, manacles, even prison cells&mdash;nothing holds him for long. Either by skill or dumb luck, your hero always gets away, eventually.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Legends of Steel</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_04a7imn3lagw","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ra4EhEl408XbssCP"}
{"name":"Focus","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Wielding arcane power has its drawbacks, but some people learn to keep their focus even when things don't go right.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">If a character with this Edge is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.5Qbb2JuTeN4XHgH5]{Shaken} as a result of failing to invoke a spell, he gets an immediate @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.9IwLt34etK096UAK]{Spirit} roll at &ndash;2 to recover.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Any), Spirit d6+, arcane skill d8+"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_pi4ivmcmcvb","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"sGLn95j2Gc5nDECC"}
{"name":"Primal Fury","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Some half-orcs or orcs have an animal rage inside them they can trigger consciously. A half-orc or orc with Prinal Fury may spend a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.LORAV4BtcI1ONG0C]{Benny} to activate his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.d0YwZF1Sf0cJgxJ4]{Berserk} Edge.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Half-orc or Orc, Berserk"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_rht8q8pjow","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"snRRjp1I4ZEnHc42"}
{"name":"Fanaticism","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>This Edge is most appropriate for members of the military, but the leader of a seasoned band of monster hunters might develop it as well.</p>\n<p>Troops under command of a character with this Edge add +2 to their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.VEsADnXDGeBjc54c]{Fear} checks and subtract 2 from rolls on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Yi3wpVNTWVajEWaQ]{Fear Table}.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Fervor"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_v523ge7encp","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Leadership Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"uiQ9tn05LNEPNvmP"}
{"name":"Scamper","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Halflings are small and quick. Some make great use of this in combat too, scampering about to avoid the blows of larger foes. Opponents of man-size or larger subtract 1 from attack rolls against halflings with this Edge. The benefit only applies when the character is aware the attack is coming, he is unbound and able to move freely, and has no encumbrance penalty.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Halfling, Agility d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_rht8q8pjow","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"vlMcEz2yPQMxP1VV"}
{"name":"Master Storyteller","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Tales of brave heroes and epic battles are told across Khorvaire in taverns and around hearths and campfires. Most master storytellers are skalds or bards.</p>\n<p>When using the Variable Glory Awards rules (p. 100), the characters roll d8s instead of a d6s if this hero recounts their deeds.</p>\n<p>In addition, the storyteller is adept at deflecting bad press through carefully chosen words. The party suffers no penalties to Glory if the storyteller rolls a critical failure, treating it as a regular failure.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source; Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Smarts d8+, Persuasion d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_04a7imn3lagw","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"vlrIFisLD7FGXUZr"}
{"name":"Arcane Background (Magecraft)","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><strong>Arcane Skill: </strong>Magecraft (Smarts)</p>\n<p><strong>Starting Powers: </strong>2</p>\n<p><strong>Power Points: </strong>15</p>\n<p><strong>Powers:</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Backlash: </strong>A Critical Failure on a magecraft roll cases the magewright a level of Fatigue and all currently active powers are terminated. Optionally you may be called to roll on the Malfunction Backlash Table.</p>\n<h2>Artificers of Eberron</h2>\n<p><em>Magecrafting </em>is simply a renaming of Weird Science to better fit Eberron. Magecraft is the creation of arcane devices as a form of arcane science through an understanding and manipulation of the magic inherent to the world of Eberron. Characters in Eberron with this Arcane Background are referred to as artificers or magewrights.</p>\n<p><em>Magecraft </em>cannot use the <strong>Jury Rig </strong>feature of Weird Science.</p>\n<p>Artificers and magewrights use strange and powerful inventions beyond the normal technological level of the setting. Such creations might be possible due to super fuels, alien discoveries, or the raw intellect of rare super-geniuses who push the boundaries of science.</p>\n<h2>Trappings</h2>\n<p>Trappings (SWADE page 150) for magecraft must always include the item they're associated with. The burst power might manifest through a rod with the head of a dragon shooting a gout of dragon's breath, while \"Marcomanoi's Wondrous Restorative Elixir!\" is a healing potion.</p>\n<p>Inventors must have their devices at hand to activate their powers.</p>\n<h2>Sharing Creations</h2>\n<p>Other characters can't activate the inventor's creations. They might not understand the strange mechanisms required to make it work, the device might not be \"calibrated\" or portioned for other users, or it might just \"fritz out\" for anyone but the creator. While this may seem a bit strange narratively, the \"magic\"-and the Power Points-come from the inventor so he must be the one to activate it.</p>\n<p>Creating devices for others is possible-it just requires an Arcane Device and the Artificer Edge.</p>\n<p>The inventor can use his devices on others, of course, including administering drinks from his magical elixirs or giving them injections of some miraculous super serum he's created. If Dr. Gabriel administers his elixir, for example, he rolls to activate the power normally. If he gives someone the bottle to use later, they'll find it's lost its potency.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nth9juzzfye","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"wLgGbaLP541KdtqR"}
{"name":"Close Fighting","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>This Edge is for skilled knife-fighters, who pride themselves on defeating their foes up close and personal.</p>\n<p>Close fighters move inside most weapons' reach, adding a bonus to their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.1oRpVdlhWTK1fR5u]{Parry} equal to the enemy weapon's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.XfWDGAU17hRz00HV]{Reach} +1 for that particular foe. No bonus is granted if the foe is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.FPyJrvPADnjDq6aD]{unarmed} or using a knife or other small weapon.</p>\n<p class=\"embedded-example\"><strong>Example: </strong>A Lhazaar pirate with Close Fighting battles a Lyrandar heir with a cutlass ( @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.XfWDGAU17hRz00HV]{Reach} 0 ). The pirates @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.1oRpVdlhWTK1fR5u]{Parry} is raised by +1.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Lankhmar, City of Thieves</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d8+, Fighting d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nslc8pagbdr","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"x0UU8bG3g095WjqQ"}
{"name":"Improved Giant Killer","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Instead of gaining +1d6 damage on an attack roll against creatures three sizes or more larger, the character may choose to ignore their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.QyUeYxvX3yjnuH25]{Armor} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.UmewRLXJsddUxY5X]{Size}. This Edge does not work with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.5LE0KnNes1Zok7XR]{area effect attacks}.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic, Giant Killer"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nslc8pagbdr","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"xs0Jm8NQrvcydchj"}
{"name":"Improved Sunder","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Dwarves have an instinctual knowledge of materials. Those with this Edge know just where to strike objects or armored foes to cause the most damage. Any weapon in the hands of a dwarf with this Edge ignores 2 point of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.QyUeYxvX3yjnuH25]{armor} (in addition to any @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.wIG7zjXqXMDDKdiJ]{AP} value the weapon may already have) on a successful hit. If the dwarf gets a raise on the attack roll, he ignores 4 points of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.QyUeYxvX3yjnuH25]{armor}. The Edge applies against all forms of armor, natural or magical.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Sunder"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_rht8q8pjow","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"xysGsSMMrLboz2Yt"}
{"name":"Finely  Tuned","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>The artificer has studied under the best masters in his field and has fine tuned his creations to maximum efficiency.</p>\n<p>When creating an <strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.UDWnUoqpSdpkWhsV]{Arcane Device}</strong>, each raise an artificer gets on his activation roll reduces the cost of the power by 1 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.ZUQ9fsJ5ybqBIByu]{Power Point}, to a minimum of 1. The Arcane Device must have the full points available to use the power in the first place before rolling. You only need to take this Edge once, not for each Arcane Device.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Slipstream Player's Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Artificer, Smarts d8+, Repair d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_pi4ivmcmcvb","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"y76KEIkaC26hQw55"}
